{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1519", "repo": "rails", "body": "This is happening in edge (master) and 3.0.7, that I am using currently.\r\nIn 3.0.7 there is also additional similar issue: if there is a `default_scope joins(:association)`, `update_all` produces sql like:\r\n```UPDATE `base_table_name` SET `updated_at` = ? WHERE `id` = ? JOIN `association_table_name` ON ...```\r\nand results in error \"column `updated_at` is ambiguous\". However, this particular bug not found in edge.\r\n\r\nI'd say that this happens since e4943e93 where current `touch` implementation was introduced, but I've tested only in 3.0.7 and master.", "_id": {"$oid": "52385406bd3543c15101193f"}, "issue_id": 1519, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1314254", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1519#issuecomment-1314254", "updated_at": "2011-06-07T08:04:27Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko", "login": "dmitriy-kiriyenko", "gravatar_id": "c4486876726bcef5b87268564fc29e6c", "html_url": "https://github.com/dmitriy-kiriyenko", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c4486876726bcef5b87268564fc29e6c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F815d8c98c8513891669c2f1af6ca4c27.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy-kiriyenko/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 124430, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dmitriy